1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,840
You have to live
to make amends for what you did.

2
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:47,120
Stars shine in the dark.

3
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,600
So you have to be brave like a star.

4
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,600
Don't give up, Mr. Trai.

5
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,680
Darin! Are you crazy?

6
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,280
How about being your woman too?

7
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,760
You bought a new phone?

8
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:01,600
Rachen bought this for you?

9
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:05,960
If you want authority, then go work.

10
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:09,120
<i>Get ready to serve Be Rich's</i>
<i>second-generation owner,</i>

11
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,040
<i>Mr. Board Member.</i>

12
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:15,840
<i>A business that looks down on customers,</i>
<i>doesn't love them, doesn't help them grow,</i>

13
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:16,760
will never ever prosper.

14
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,040
Trai! You just wanted to show everyone

15
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,040
I was terrible at raising my kid.

16
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,360
Stop seeing Trai. How much do you want?

17
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,760
Are you paying by check or cash?

18
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,600
<i>Mr. Tritot, how much do you think</i>

19
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,920
<i>your son is worth?</i>

20
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,720
Oh, hey.

21
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:50,240
Why are you here?

22
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,320
30 million?

23
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,720
You asked my father for 30 million?

24
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:05,480
So you just sold
our friendship like that, Pakbung?

25
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,560
- You heard that?
- Yeah.

26
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,240
I'm really disappointed in you.

27
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,240
If you're gonna eavesdrop,
at least listen to the whole thing.

28
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,080
You're even more money hungry
than I thought.

29
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:29,320
Well, I don't know how to deny that.

30
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,960
So shall we start?

31
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,680
I'll ask three questions. That's it.

32
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,120
Huh?

33
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:39,200
First question,
what's Mr. Trai's favorite food?

34
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,200
You think I'm here to play with you?

35
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:44,880
If you don't know, I'll take that
as permission to keep seeing him.

36
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:50,360
Spaghetti with clams,
paired with white wine.

37
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,560
Wrong. It's grilled intestines.

38
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:01,080
I saw you eat
three plates all by yourself.

39
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,720
But I didn't have proof,

40
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,560
so your dad didn't believe me.

41
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,720
Why did you…

42
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:16,520
Yeah, money can buy me.

43
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,000
But I get to choose the buyers.

44
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,440
What was question two?

45
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,160
Do you snore?

46
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,360
Your dad called me an idiot.

47
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:36,280
Ms. Darin said you snore.

48
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,360
Then Da got it right.

49
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,520
Wrong.

50
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:45,600
You grind your teeth when you sleep.

51
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,360
Your teeth must be cracking.

52
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:04,280
How stressed do you have to be
to grind your teeth this loudly?

53
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,520
So that's why my teeth hurt
when I wake up sometimes.

54
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:16,040
Want to pre-order a mouth guard from me?

55
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,440
I can get it for you.

56
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,920
You can sell anything, huh?

57
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,080
And question three?

58
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,760
This one's the easiest.

59
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,840
What's your dream?

60
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,320
No way my dad could answer that.

61
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,280
You wanted to be
a world-class soccer player, didn't you?

62
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:37,720
Your dad remembers
what you wanted to be as a kid.

63
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,360
He remembers things about you.

64
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,400
The info might not be updated,

65
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,280
but he's never forgotten
anything about you.

66
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,920
Even if his methods
aren't exactly what you'd want,

67
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,240
I'm honestly so jealous of you.

68
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,360
Your dad

69
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,920
really cares about you, Mr. Trai.

70
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,080
Do I really know nothing
about you at all, Trai?

71
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:20,920
<i>You couldn't answer</i>
<i>a single question, Mr. Tritot.</i>

72
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:25,000
So I'll keep
being Mr. Trai's friend, okay?

73
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,600
I just want him to have a safe zone.

74
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,840
Don't worry.
I'm not trying to scam him for money.

75
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:38,440
I've tried plenty of times already,
but he always sees through it.

76
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:42,920
I guess experience taught him well.

77
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:52,680
Honestly, I really admire you, Mr. Tritot.

78
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:55,800
I've read your biography.

79
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:59,360
You're my idol.

80
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:03,680
I want to be smart.
I want to be rich like you.

81
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:07,720
But if I ever succeed like you did,

82
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:10,560
I'll remember your parenting style

83
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,080
and make sure never to use it.

84
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,920
I don't want my child to have everything

85
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,200
yet still be unhappy like Mr. Trai.

86
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:11,400
So, meeting someone money can't buy
really shocked you that much?

87
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,920
Pakbung really is unpredictable.

88
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,040
I don't think

89
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,560
she's that hard to figure out.

90
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:32,640
She just wants more out of Trai,

91
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,640
just like you.

92
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:40,640
Start as friends,

93
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,280
end with condoms.

94
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,960
So what are you going to do?

95
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,680
Are you going to get her to marry you too?

96
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,400
That's a good idea.

97
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,800
All of Trai's women…

98
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,160
are impressive.

99
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,960
You're disgusting.

100
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,040
Disgusting?

101
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,640
Am I so disgusting?

102
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:27,720
Then why don't you leave?

103
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:32,640
Why keep leeching off
someone so disgusting?

104
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:38,480
You know what that's called?

105
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,840
A tick.

106
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:47,040
Isn't that even more disgusting?
You keep leeching off others.

107
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,920
Shameless.

108
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,360
So everything's settled?

109
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:46,480
Why didn't you tell me from the start

110
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,040
that Pakbung didn't take my dad's money?

111
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,560
You didn't ask.

112
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:56,680
- I didn't ask?
- No.

113
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:59,320
Hey. Come eat already.
The pork's almost gone.

114
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,240
Yeah, hurry up.

115
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,120
Niuniu.

116
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,480
You eat meat now?

117
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,480
- Shit!
- Oh, yeah.

118
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,520
I forgot!

119
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,520
I gotta go spit it out.

120
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,200
Oh…

121
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,520
So, you didn't sell him?

122
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,400
So you're possessive, huh?

123
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,760
I didn't like the buyer.

124
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,840
Then who do you like?

125
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,760
Ow, Bung!

126
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,320
Thank you for not selling me.

127
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,800
Well…

128
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,480
we're friends.

129
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,240
Just friends?

130
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,760
Ow! Bung!

131
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,720
That was loud.

132
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,640
Pakbung.

133
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,240
What kind of friend is that expensive?

134
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,360
Usually, 300,000's enough for you.

135
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,760
But 30 million
and you still wouldn't sell?

136
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:17,720
Yeah.

137
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,560
Forget 300,000.

138
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,120
- Just--
- Take this.

139
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,480
Eat properly.

140
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:24,120
You're making a mess, Kanah.

141
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,240
Bung!

142
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:33,720
Mr. Trai.

143
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:37,280
Didn't you have something to give Pakbung?

144
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:57,000
<i>Trash like you can't win against my mom.</i>

145
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:02,000
<i>But you assaulted my friend.</i>
<i>You have to take legal responsibility.</i>

146
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:05,320
<i>Even if I killed your friend,</i>
<i>I still wouldn't be guilty of anything.</i>

147
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:08,560
That's a killer scene.

148
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,360
Can I post this?

149
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,200
- No.
- What?

150
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,560
Keep it until the time is right.

151
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:24,000
Oh, like,

152
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,960
a trump card or something?

153
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:26,920
Yeah.

154
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:31,080
Just in case something happens,
which I hope it won't.

155
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:32,600
But if it does,

156
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,720
you'll have a weapon
to negotiate with those people.

157
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,000
Thank you, Mr. Trai.

158
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:45,960
Well…

159
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,200
we're friends.

160
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,760
<i>They live in comfort</i>

161
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,760
<i>while we're bleeding our eyes out</i>
<i>just to survive.</i>

162
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:21,040
<i>They can send their kids</i>
<i>to higher education,</i>

163
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,680
<i>but we can barely pay</i>
<i>our children's school fees.</i>

164
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:26,600
<i>Don't let them</i>
<i>make a living off our suffering.</i>

165
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:27,320
‪TRAI. DIE.

166
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,880
<i>They can't be happy</i>
<i>while we're the ones in pain.</i>

167
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:30,600
‪YOU DESERVE TO DIE.

168
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,040
<i>We'll take everything back from them!</i>

169
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,200
SCAM COMPANY

170
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,960
- Come out!
- Come here and face us!

171
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,600
You're killing us!

172
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,640
You took my house!

173
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:45,200
- Yes!
- Give it back!

174
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,920
- You make money off other people's misery!
- Yeah!

175
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,400
Give my father's land back!

176
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:52,680
- Yes!
- Give it back!

177
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,960
Tritot, you tricked me into investing.

178
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,360
You lied to me!

179
00:15:57,440 --> 00:16:01,920
- You lied to me!
- You lied to us! Come out!

180
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,440
- Come out! Come out! Come out, Tritot!
- Come here!

181
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:10,000
- You bloodsucker!
- You took our money!

182
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,200
You bloodsucker!

183
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:16,240
- Come out!
- I said come out!

184
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,200
Go get your boss…

185
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:18,160
Hey.

186
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,400
That car, the fancy one.

187
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,720
It's definitely Tritot's.

188
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,560
Why the hell are these people here?

189
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:27,480
- Hey!
- Go get him!

190
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:32,800
Tritot!

191
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,680
- Come out!
- Out of the car!

192
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,200
Get out of the car!

193
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:38,400
Come out!

194
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,320
- Move.
- Mr. Rachen.

195
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:42,840
Clear them out! Now!

196
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:45,480
- Come out!
- You're shameless!

197
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:46,400
Get out of the car!

198
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,680
Give my life back!

199
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:48,760
Come out!

200
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:49,920
Tritot, come out!

201
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,760
What the hell?!

202
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,240
Huh?

203
00:16:58,880 --> 00:16:59,800
Trai.

204
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,400
You're protesting because you want
to talk to the executives, right?

205
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,800
I'm right here.

206
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,800
- Hey!
- Let's go!

207
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:11,119
Hey, don't go over there.
Stay here and take care of my dad. Now!

208
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,720
I'm Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

209
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,560
son of the owner of this company.

210
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,760
I'm a partner here too. So if you've got
something to say, talk to me.

211
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:21,599
Now? I've wanted
to talk to you for a long time,

212
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,160
but all you did was hound us for debt,

213
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,920
and now we've got nothing left.

214
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,880
- Yes!
- Give it back!

215
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:29,040
- Give back my money!
- Give it!

216
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:30,840
I can sort this out.

217
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:33,280
But if you won't talk,
then you won't get anything back.

218
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,120
Trai.

219
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,840
- Dad…
- That's Tritot.

220
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,840
Get inside. Now.

221
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,240
Back off! Come here!

222
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:43,280
Don't come any closer!

223
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,760
- Don't come closer.
- Dad.

224
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,440
Don't come closer.

225
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,040
Don't come closer! Don't come closer.

226
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:50,280
Please, calm down.

227
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:53,360
So you finally came out?
I've been waiting to see you for ages.

228
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,960
You people never cared about us.

229
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,920
I lost money because of you.

230
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,840
I'm ruined because of you.

231
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:03,800
I bought stocks like you advertised
and look what happened.

232
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,320
- Calm down.
- You scammed me.

233
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,360
You lied to us!

234
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:10,600
Wait, listen to me first.
We only provided loans,

235
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:12,800
and we did marketing partnerships
with those stock companies.

236
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,800
We didn't scam you.
Don't misunderstand, please.

237
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:18,360
Because I believed you,
I believed your company.

238
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:19,920
This is what you did to me?!

239
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,880
Wait. Please, calm down. How about this?

240
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,720
We'll arrange
a legal team to help you sue.

241
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:28,440
Those companies, stocks, crypto,

242
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:31,520
they've all fled overseas already!
Who are we supposed to sue?

243
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,280
Yes!

244
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,040
So you're dumping more burden on us?

245
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:40,520
Aren't we carrying enough burden now? Why?

246
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,320
Why do you get to live comfortably

247
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,760
on our blood, sweat and tears?!

248
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:46,680
Yes!

249
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,760
- Argh!
- Hey!

250
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:51,560
- Stop!
- Kill him!

251
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:52,720
I said stop!

252
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:56,400
I'll take responsibility myself.

253
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:59,480
Even if Be Rich isn't
the company that scammed you,

254
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:02,520
we still failed to provide
investment information.

255
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,440
So this is our responsibility too.

256
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:10,280
We will suspend debt payments
until you can get back on your feet.

257
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:12,160
And the assets we seized,

258
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:15,200
we will consider giving them back
to you so you can make a living.

259
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,960
We'll set up a legal team

260
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:20,960
to help you fight this to the end,
and we will get your money back.

261
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:23,720
Can he really do that?

262
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,200
And I promise.

263
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:28,640
We will stand by you,
and we will never abandon you.

264
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,360
To the press, record this.

265
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:36,000
I'm Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

266
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,600
son of Mr. Tritot.

267
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,160
I promise

268
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:44,400
I will compensate everyone
who lost assets from crypto and stocks.

269
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,280
And I won't press charges
against any of you.

270
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:48,160
In the past, Be Rich made mistakes.

271
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,280
We cared too little about our customers.

272
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:53,280
But this incident
will be what forces us to change.

273
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:56,040
From now on,
Be Rich will stand by all of you.

274
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:00,080
And as a partner,

275
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,960
I apologize from the bottom of my heart.

276
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,040
WE WANT JUSTICE

277
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,280
Hey!

278
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,800
Hey, hey.

279
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,280
Stop, stop.

280
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,520
Don't do anything to him.
Let's talk it out.

281
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,520
Dad, are you okay?

282
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:52,920
Trai, get inside.

283
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,720
We did nothing wrong,
yet you admitted fault,

284
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,400
bowed to those people,

285
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,080
and even said you'd compensate them.

286
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,320
How do you think
the public will see Be Rich now?

287
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,520
My father had a knife to his back.

288
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,880
But you made promises
without consulting the board.

289
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:38,040
If we can't deliver,
it'll become an even bigger disaster.

290
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:40,400
Then we'll deliver.
What's so hard about that?

291
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:45,480
Make a list of every customer
who lost out from this campaign.

292
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:46,560
See what we seized from them.

293
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,280
If any seized asset
is essential to their survival

294
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:52,040
or their livelihood,

295
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:55,040
we let them take it back first.
That's all.

296
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,040
But some of those assets
have already been sold into the market.

297
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,040
Then buy them back.

298
00:21:58,920 --> 00:21:59,760
Mr. Tritot,

299
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,600
your son is destroying our company.

300
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:09,080
Excuse me.

301
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:14,760
Since the news about Mr. Trai went out,

302
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:18,040
Be Rich's stock price has risen by 86.67%.

303
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:20,240
The online sentiment is positive too.

304
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,920
Everyone's praising Mr. Trai's thinking,

305
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,920
saying this is the new era for Be Rich.

306
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,240
Dad.

307
00:22:57,200 --> 00:23:01,200
I don't agree with Trai making promises
to the crowd without the board's consent.

308
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:05,040
Making a unilateral decision like that
only hurts Be Rich's interests.

309
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,960
I always thought
Trai didn't care about work.

310
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,080
Turns out

311
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,360
he studied everything in detail.

312
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:23,480
Have you ever tried thinking
about management the way Trai does?

313
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:28,360
Trai's management approach? What?

314
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:31,960
Like, giving in to the people
who messed up but blame others?

315
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:35,320
Letting people who use violence
to get their way win?

316
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,520
Admitting fault
even though we're not wrong,

317
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:40,920
risking hundreds of millions in losses?
That kind of approach, Dad?

318
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:42,680
No.

319
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,840
Understanding customers.

320
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:51,000
Having empathy like they're family.

321
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:56,160
Being a company that doesn't profit
off other people's suffering.

322
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,280
So, you agree with Trai?

323
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:12,040
Trai's approach might be
Be Rich's next step forward.

324
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,200
If you let Trai come in
and run this place,

325
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:18,840
I'll resign.

326
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:24,600
What's wrong with you?

327
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:26,520
Are you going to choose Trai or me?

328
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,280
Why do I have to choose?

329
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,640
Stop being dramatic, will you?

330
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:33,520
I just want to know.

331
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,800
Do I still matter to you?

332
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:41,320
Now that Trai's back,
do I still have any value to you at all?

333
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:44,480
Don't be ridiculous.

334
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:47,480
Why the hell can't brothers work together?

335
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,280
Or do you want to be number one?

336
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:53,960
You want to be chairman instead of me?

337
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:57,400
Fine. Take my seat.

338
00:24:58,120 --> 00:24:59,800
Go on, take my seat.

339
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:02,920
You want my company that badly, don't you?
Go on, sit there.

340
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,680
Dad…

341
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:15,120
I gave everything for you.

342
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:20,800
And you can dismiss my love that coldly?

343
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:38,440
In that meeting, Tritot didn't say a word.

344
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,400
He was probably still stunned,

345
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,800
getting hit by his own son's attitude.

346
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:47,000
He agrees with his son, that's what it is.

347
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:51,360
And the moment the other executives saw
the stock price shoot up, they went quiet.

348
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:54,400
Trai is making my plan
more difficult to achieve.

349
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,320
Why do you think of me like that, Dad?

350
00:26:20,960 --> 00:26:23,080
Are you here trying to be
a lightning rod or something?

351
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:29,200
Oh? Don't look so shocked.

352
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:31,680
You're the one who asked me to come.

353
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,880
400…

354
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:50,320
Here, this month's phone installment.

355
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,080
500 baht.

356
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:59,680
Here. If you don't want bills
and coins next time,

357
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,360
then let me transfer it to you.

358
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:03,640
If you transfer it,
you have to do it in front of me.

359
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:08,120
You really want to see me that badly?

360
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,280
Yes.

361
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:20,720
You always show up
at the right place, at the right time.

362
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,360
I fought with my dad.

363
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:36,320
But honestly… it wasn't really a fight.

364
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,800
- It was more like…
- Feeling hurt?

365
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,720
I'm not Mr. Tritot's biological son.

366
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,280
My real dad left my mom and me

367
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:57,880
before I was even born.

368
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:02,080
My mom raised me as best as she could.

369
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,080
Then when I was twelve,

370
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:06,600
me and my mom met Mr. Tritot.

371
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,760
The first time I saw him,

372
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:13,000
he looked so cool.

373
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,880
He was the only person I respected so much

374
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:18,920
that I wanted him to be my real dad.

375
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:24,760
Then… how did you end up
living with Mr. Tritot?

376
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:31,000
Honestly? My mom sold me to him.

377
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:36,640
She was obsessed with a new guy
and didn't want to raise me anymore.

378
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:40,760
Dad… I mean Mr. Tritot,

379
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:44,040
went and talked to her
because he didn't want me to be an orphan.

380
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:47,560
So in the end,

381
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:52,480
my mom gave me to Mr. Tritot
in exchange for a lump sum.

382
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:55,120
That's called being sold, right?

383
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:02,000
What? Do you pity me?

384
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:06,480
No…

385
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:09,080
You have value.

386
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:10,960
You had a price.

387
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:14,120
For me, when my dad left me,

388
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:18,360
no one had to pay him anything.
He just walked out.

389
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:24,120
He threw me away like soggy trash.

390
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:36,360
Shall we try going higher?

391
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:39,160
Maybe,

392
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:42,800
when you look down from up there,
your problems will get smaller.

393
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:48,800
Smaller?

394
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,560
If I were just a little higher,

395
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,160
maybe I wouldn't have to envy Trai.

396
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:13,720
<i>I apologize to everyone</i>
<i>from the bottom of my heart.</i>

397
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:14,640
MR. TRAI BOWORNMONGKOLPHONG
SON OF BE RICH LEASING'S CHAIRMAN

398
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,400
Wow, Trai,

399
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,960
you were so damn cool.

400
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:22,760
Look at the news. So cool.

401
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:26,400
Why don't you act handsome
and cool like that every day?

402
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,680
Huh? What have I been
this whole time then?

403
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:29,920
You're like an old uncle next door.

404
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:34,360
- Lee.
- Oh, sorry…

405
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:36,920
You're handsome, sure,

406
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:39,000
but you look like
you're living off my sister.

407
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,200
Whoa, that's harsh.

408
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:46,200
So what work is your sister doing?
Why isn't she back yet?

409
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,240
No idea.

410
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:03,400
Speak of the devil

411
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,360
and she will appear.

412
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,560
Mr. Trai.

413
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:09,400
Why are you here?

414
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,040
Whoa, Pakbung.

415
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,440
How can you call Trai like that?

416
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:17,720
No respect at all.
He's a top executive now.

417
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:18,600
Hey, not yet.

418
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,560
But you're on every channel.

419
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,680
"Be Rich's new blood."

420
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,680
So you went back to work with your dad.

421
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,120
Not gonna do the school anymore?

422
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:31,360
I am.

423
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:35,000
I just went to Be Rich for a day or two,

424
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,640
trying to mess things up,
so Dad would stop dragging me into work.

425
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,560
You know,
almost all the executives hate me.

426
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,440
I'll probably get fired in a bit.

427
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:59,280
I thought I might have the fortune

428
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:02,360
of being friends
with a high-level executive.

429
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,880
Oh, dream on, Sis.

430
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:08,160
If Trai really goes back up there,

431
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,080
why would he still be friends with you?

432
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,040
You're seriously delusional.

433
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,000
Right, Trai?

434
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:21,480
Kanah, did you take out the trash yet?

435
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,800
I'll do it.

436
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:34,360
Pakbung. Pakbung.

437
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:46,040
Why did you say that?

438
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:51,560
It was a chemical catalyst.

439
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:55,200
All chemical reactions
that affect the heart

440
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,240
need a catalyst.

441
00:32:58,480 --> 00:33:01,760
Otherwise, it might happen too slowly
or never happen at all.

442
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:04,920
I'm just speeding it up a little.

443
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:06,920
Hey.

444
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:09,280
Hey.

445
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:12,560
Hey.

446
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:15,440
Are you afraid I'll leave you?

447
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,920
What?

448
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,800
You're afraid I'll run off
to work with my dad

449
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:21,840
and stop being friends with you, right?

450
00:33:21,920 --> 00:33:24,360
You're the one
who wanted us to be friends.

451
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:28,840
If you want to end it,
what am I supposed to do?

452
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:55,480
I'm never gonna stop
being friends with you.

453
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:59,560
Everything started with me,

454
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:02,000
so I'm damn sure of one thing.

455
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:06,280
Between us, it'll never end because of me.

456
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,280
It'll be you.

457
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:15,639
I don't cut people off easily either.

458
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,520
Good.

459
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:22,239
Then let's stay friends for a long time.
Like, forever,

460
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:24,800
until we're old and our gums
are falling out. How's that?

461
00:34:27,159 --> 00:34:30,800
Then whoever ends this first
is nothing but a dog.

462
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:33,719
Okay.

463
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:36,080
Deal.

464
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:40,480
Deal.

465
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:53,560
Don't let go of my hand so easily,
Pakbung.

466
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:56,639
Pay me a 100 million,
and I still won't let go.

467
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:38,600
Where the hell
have you been screwing around?

468
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:41,480
Why are you just back now?

469
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:49,920
I saw the news already. If you're pissed
about work, don't take it out on me.

470
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,240
I'm asking. Where did you go?

471
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,000
I went to look for a job.

472
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:06,760
My friend's an agent,
so I went to a casting. Satisfied?

473
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,120
No.

474
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:10,320
Everyone knows you're my wife.

475
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,880
Why are you looking for work?

476
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:14,080
Planning to sell yourself or something?

477
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:17,240
I'm not selling myself. I want to work.

478
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:20,120
I want to have value.
I want to feel useful.

479
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,400
If you don't want me working elsewhere,

480
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:24,920
then let me work at Be Rich.

481
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,400
Someone like you?

482
00:36:27,720 --> 00:36:29,000
What would you even do there?

483
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:33,080
So what? You want me trapped
in this house forever?

484
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,920
I'm bored. I want to see the world.

485
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:38,680
You don't need to see the world.

486
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:40,600
Just opening one thing is enough.

487
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:45,000
What? Are you gonna slap me?

488
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:45,920
Disgusting.

489
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:49,320
When I do nothing,
you call me a tick clinging to you.

490
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:51,640
When I try to get a job,
you block me again.

491
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:54,640
Are you a psychopath?

492
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:56,320
How much more are you going to crush me?

493
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:58,360
If you need something to vent on,

494
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,480
I'll buy you a sex doll.

495
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:07,000
A sex doll? Why would I need a sex doll?

496
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:11,440
I already paid good money
for a doll like you.

497
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:12,640
Why would I need a sex doll?

498
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:15,560
Let go! Don't touch me. Let go!

499
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:33,040
Working in bed is a lot easier.

500
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,000
I'm not a prostitute!

501
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:15,320
Help me. I can't take it anymore.

502
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,160
I hate them.

503
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:20,720
I hate them.

504
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,600
I hate them!

505
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:30,520
I won't let this family
destroy my life again.

506
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,440
Is this the page?

507
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:46,520
Someone created an Anti-Be Rich page,

508
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:50,080
posting content to rally people
who hate Be Rich to protest, sir.

509
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:51,000
SCAMMER DISGUISED AS LOAN APP

510
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:54,320
The crowd that came that day
was probably mobilized by this page.

511
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,040
Who made it?

512
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:58,640
We still can't trace it.

513
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,280
The protection is extremely tight.

514
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,920
This isn't a regular internet user.

515
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:07,120
If they don't have money,
then they've got serious knowledge.

516
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:09,600
Or they must really hate me.

517
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:18,920
What about the hitman thing?
Did the investigator get back to you?

518
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:21,960
He did. He'll send the details tonight.

519
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:27,720
And the thing I told you to prepare?

520
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,720
All set, sir.

521
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:52,440
You've seen the news, right?

522
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:57,720
The media is hyping Trai hard,
calling him Be Rich's new hope.

523
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:01,000
Yes, I saw it.

524
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:03,320
A fake hope, if you ask me.

525
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:06,000
You're the one

526
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:08,600
who's more fit to own Be Rich, Rachen.

527
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:12,800
Be Rich operates on reality.

528
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:14,960
Your brother is a dream-seller.

529
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:17,720
He's too idealistic.
He's not suited for our world.

530
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:21,920
Are you really going to let
your brother run Be Rich?

531
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:27,040
That should be up to Dad
and the other board members.

532
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:31,560
You do know

533
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:35,440
most of the board
is on my mom's side, right?

534
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:39,960
And my mom is backing you.

535
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,080
I know.

536
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:46,120
Thank you,
Mrs. Mookmanee, for trusting me.

537
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,440
Because I trust you,

538
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:51,840
that's why I brought
the majority to your side.

539
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:56,080
Now there's only
one person left, the chairman.

540
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:04,320
You two didn't really have to follow me.
I'm just repainting the school a bit.

541
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:06,720
How could we possibly let you do it alone?

542
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:21,760
Dad?

543
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:23,720
Mr. Tritot.

544
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:26,680
Are you okay, sir?

545
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:27,880
What are you doing here?

546
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:31,120
You're hanging the lights?

547
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,720
Yeah, yeah. Hanging lights.

548
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:35,000
All by yourself?

549
00:41:35,080 --> 00:41:38,560
Let me do it, sir.
Where do you want them hung?

550
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:49,920
Since your mom passed away…

551
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:54,240
I haven't come back here.

552
00:41:58,240 --> 00:41:59,240
So why today?

553
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:08,960
Trai…

554
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:11,120
about everything in the past,

555
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,040
I'm sorry.

556
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:20,960
Am I dreaming or what?

557
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:24,760
You came here, talked about Mom,

558
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:27,000
and just now you apologized to me?

559
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:29,360
Yes.

560
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:33,840
When I first started Be Rich,

561
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,480
it was because I understood

562
00:42:36,560 --> 00:42:40,400
how it feels when someone
desperately needs money

563
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,960
but has none.

564
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:46,720
I poured everything into Be Rich.

565
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:50,560
I loved it so much.

566
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:55,200
But in the end,
I forgot my original intention.

567
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:04,360
If Be Rich were in the hands
of someone who truly intends well,

568
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:06,440
who truly understands it

569
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:08,960
like you,

570
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:14,520
our company would probably grow
with far more dignity.

571
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:18,680
If you can build this school for your mom,

572
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:22,680
can you also build Be Rich for me?

573
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:34,240
I've never thought
about running Be Rich at all, Dad.

574
00:43:37,120 --> 00:43:38,320
Alright, that's fine.

575
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:40,880
No need to answer now.

576
00:43:42,520 --> 00:43:43,440
Take your time to think.

577
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:45,680
Whether you do it or not,

578
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:48,600
I won't force you.

579
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:51,560
And from now on,

580
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:54,440
I won't force you ever again.

581
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:00,280
This is like a new Tritot.

582
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:04,640
How long can you stay like this?

583
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:06,960
You're not chaining me up
again tomorrow, right?

584
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:10,800
I told you I'm sorry.

585
00:44:11,680 --> 00:44:12,600
Believe me.

586
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:14,760
I won't force you anymore.

587
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:16,880
Come on, just give it a try.

588
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:24,200
Should I turn the lights on now?

589
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:26,000
Go ahead.

590
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:28,160
Alright.

591
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:32,160
Look. Yay!

592
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:33,760
- Yay!
- Wow.

593
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:34,880
It's done.

594
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:36,960
It's so beautiful.

595
00:44:37,480 --> 00:44:39,840
What do you think? I did it.

596
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:41,520
I helped too.

597
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,480
- Wow.
- He helped a lot.

598
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:45,440
You're both amazing.

599
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:48,080
Thank you so much, my good boys.

600
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:51,040
This one too.

601
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,600
Hey, two kisses?

602
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:58,200
Here. I made your favorite fried chicken.
Let's eat.

603
00:44:58,280 --> 00:44:59,920
Let's go. Time for chicken!

604
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:10,720
I miss…

605
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:15,080
I miss times like that.

606
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:19,360
I miss your mom. I miss everything.

607
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:22,160
I really miss it all.

608
00:45:26,840 --> 00:45:27,880
Me too…

609
00:45:57,680 --> 00:45:58,800
I don't know

610
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:02,600
when things started to go wrong.

611
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:07,320
I really don't.

612
00:46:10,080 --> 00:46:11,720
But in your heart,

613
00:46:13,640 --> 00:46:15,920
I'm a terrible father, right?

614
00:46:17,520 --> 00:46:18,400
Right?

615
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:25,920
I wasn't a very good son either.

616
00:46:29,040 --> 00:46:30,080
I'm sorry, Dad.

617
00:46:37,440 --> 00:46:39,120
I'm sorry, my son.

618
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:41,720
I really am.

619
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:45,600
I'm sorry that…

620
00:46:47,280 --> 00:46:48,680
I couldn't be a good father

621
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:51,640
sooner.

622
00:46:58,520 --> 00:47:00,040
Just you understanding me,

623
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:04,600
understanding who I am,

624
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:09,960
that's already more than enough.

625
00:47:14,800 --> 00:47:16,160
I'll try my best.

626
00:47:18,680 --> 00:47:19,680
I promise.

627
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:23,080
For our family.

628
00:47:24,320 --> 00:47:25,440
Yes.

629
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:28,440
For our family,

630
00:47:30,640 --> 00:47:32,200
I'll try again.

631
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,720
It's not too late, Son.

632
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:42,360
If your mom could see this,

633
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:44,480
she'd be so happy.

634
00:47:45,680 --> 00:47:46,760
She really would be.

635
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:55,720
I'm so happy.

636
00:47:59,160 --> 00:48:00,360
Can you come back home today?

637
00:48:03,120 --> 00:48:05,600
Oh, so you already have plans.

638
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:19,560
Hello.

639
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:24,320
I just brought some bua loi.
And I'll be leaving right away.

640
00:48:24,400 --> 00:48:25,760
I didn't say anything, did I?

641
00:48:28,680 --> 00:48:30,080
Since when do you like bua loi?

642
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:32,520
Well,

643
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:35,040
since I met Pakbung.

644
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:39,560
Another new discovery.

645
00:48:41,600 --> 00:48:42,880
Bring some for me tomorrow too.

646
00:48:44,480 --> 00:48:45,800
Exactly like that.

647
00:48:45,880 --> 00:48:47,000
Sure.

648
00:48:47,080 --> 00:48:50,640
50 baht per bowl, plus 10 for the egg.
Delivery fee not included.

649
00:48:53,360 --> 00:48:54,680
Alright.

650
00:48:56,920 --> 00:49:00,240
Dad, start a loyalty card with her.
Maybe she'll deliver for free.

651
00:49:01,440 --> 00:49:03,200
Sure. Let's start tomorrow.

652
00:49:06,240 --> 00:49:08,080
Shall we make
Mom's fried chicken tomorrow?

653
00:49:08,160 --> 00:49:09,160
I want to eat it.

654
00:49:10,320 --> 00:49:11,160
Sure.

655
00:49:12,160 --> 00:49:14,480
Hold on.
I think I still remember the recipe.

656
00:49:15,880 --> 00:49:16,960
But I can't promise it'll be edible.

657
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:22,000
Alright, I'll be going now.

658
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:23,920
Goodbye.

659
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:30,800
Here.

660
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:37,120
Thanks.

661
00:50:23,800 --> 00:50:27,960
<i>I found CCTV footage showing</i>
<i>the guy who set fire to the school.</i>

662
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:30,120
<i>Please take a look, Mr. Tritot.</i>

663
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:41,680
CAR PAINTING AND REPAIR SERVICE

664
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:02,800
Trai?

665
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:08,840
Darin?

666
00:51:15,040 --> 00:51:18,080
Hey, tomorrow, I want it exactly like this
again, okay? From the same place.

667
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:19,840
I want Dad to try it.

668
00:51:20,880 --> 00:51:23,040
It's the same place
I used to buy for you before.

669
00:51:23,640 --> 00:51:25,400
Oh? Really?

670
00:51:30,040 --> 00:51:33,720
I'm really happy for you that
you're on good terms with your dad now.

671
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:37,680
It really is good.

672
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:42,400
So good
that I don't even know if it's real.

673
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:47,840
Is it real now? If it's still not…

674
00:51:47,920 --> 00:51:49,440
Ah! It's real. It's real.

675
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:07,000
So, I'm allowed to hope, right?

676
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,200
Of course.

677
00:52:25,520 --> 00:52:28,000
Today, I saw your dad's eyes.

678
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:30,800
They weren't like
the last time I met him at all.

679
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:34,480
This time, I think

680
00:52:35,280 --> 00:52:38,840
you can hope as much as you want.

681
00:52:51,720 --> 00:52:53,480
Mr. Trai! Mr. Trai!

682
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:02,480
Prarop, how's Dad?

683
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:05,120
The doctor found a hematoma in his brain.
They're operating now.

684
00:53:08,440 --> 00:53:10,040
How did Mr. Tritot fall down the stairs?

685
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:11,000
I don't know either.

686
00:53:34,800 --> 00:53:37,160
Doctor, how is my father?

687
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:39,800
We performed a craniotomy,
removed the blood clot,

688
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:41,560
and managed the intracranial pressure.

689
00:53:41,640 --> 00:53:43,840
The good news is there's no more bleeding,

690
00:53:44,440 --> 00:53:45,600
and the swelling hasn't increased.

691
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:48,200
But we need to monitor him closely.

692
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:50,920
He's not young,
and he also has heart disease.

693
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:55,520
Heart disease?

694
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:58,200
Yes.
Mr. Tritot has coronary artery stenosis.

695
00:53:58,280 --> 00:54:00,480
His records shows that
he recently had a balloon angioplasty.

696
00:54:00,560 --> 00:54:03,240
A cardiologist will come
to evaluate him again.

697
00:54:03,320 --> 00:54:05,360
For now, we've moved him to the ICU.

698
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:39,720
Dad, please don't leave me.

699
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:23,440
Mr. Trai, you look exhausted.

700
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:24,720
Do you want to lie down for a bit?

701
00:55:25,320 --> 00:55:28,840
I can't sleep.
I want to wait until Dad wakes up.

702
00:55:30,160 --> 00:55:31,040
You wanna go home?

703
00:55:31,880 --> 00:55:33,280
Lee can take you.

704
00:55:34,680 --> 00:55:36,200
I'm free today.

705
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:38,560
I can stay with you.

706
00:55:52,680 --> 00:55:53,600
Your clothes, Mr. Trai.

707
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:09,360
You had to bring the maid
to look after him?

708
00:56:10,720 --> 00:56:11,640
No.

709
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:16,680
It's just…

710
00:56:17,320 --> 00:56:18,360
What?

711
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:21,160
It's…

712
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:33,160
Mr. Rachen.

713
00:56:33,240 --> 00:56:35,320
Mr. Rachen,
why didn't you answer your phone?

714
00:56:35,920 --> 00:56:37,120
Mr. Rachen.

715
00:56:37,760 --> 00:56:39,200
What the hell, Rut?

716
00:56:39,280 --> 00:56:40,560
Mr. Tritot fell down the stairs.

717
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:56,560
I'll go downstairs to see if there's food.
If anything happens, call me, okay?

718
00:57:15,640 --> 00:57:17,640
I have something
I need to tell you, Mr. Trai.

719
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:28,560
Mr. Tritot! Mr. Tritot!

720
00:57:29,080 --> 00:57:31,480
Mr. Tritot.

721
00:57:31,560 --> 00:57:33,400
Is anyone here? Help!

722
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:35,000
Mr. Tritot!

723
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:38,320
Someone pushed Dad?

724
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:40,720
I really did hear it.

725
00:57:40,800 --> 00:57:43,600
But who would've pushed him?

726
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:46,400
At that time,
there was no one in the house at all.

727
00:57:57,200 --> 00:57:59,160
Don't think I don't know
what you did to Dad.

728
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:00,240
What did I do?!

729
00:58:00,320 --> 00:58:02,440
You pushed him down the stairs.

730
00:58:02,520 --> 00:58:05,680
Because I'm not his real son, right?
So that makes me the villain?

731
00:58:05,760 --> 00:58:08,040
And you, the son who never listens to Dad,

732
00:58:08,120 --> 00:58:10,320
and that woman
who'd do anything for money,

733
00:58:10,400 --> 00:58:12,640
aren't you both also suspicious?

734
00:58:16,800 --> 00:58:19,080
<i>I was so focused on myself.</i>

735
00:58:19,640 --> 00:58:22,200
<i>I kept blaming Dad for hurting me.</i>

736
00:58:22,840 --> 00:58:24,200
<i>But actually, I was the one</i>

737
00:58:24,920 --> 00:58:26,760
who kept hurting him all along.

738
00:58:27,360 --> 00:58:29,120
I've never had
any ill intentions toward you.

739
00:58:29,200 --> 00:58:31,080
Not now. Not ever.

740
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:33,440
I'm on your side.

741
00:58:33,520 --> 00:58:34,760
I'm sorry.

742
00:58:36,160 --> 00:58:37,440
Dad, you know who the culprit was?

743
00:58:39,720 --> 00:58:40,880
Was it Rachen?

744
00:59:33,760 --> 00:59:37,120
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
